⏺ Assumptions (proceeding without clarifying questions)    

  1. Primary surface is mobile (iOS/Capacitor), laptop secondary — all layouts mobile-first                            
  2. "Current week" = the week containing today, even if incomplete
  3. Baseline = CTL (42-day exponentially-weighted TSS average), already in fitness-model.ts                           
  4. Injury risk = output from injury/engine.ts — already has a risk level                                           
  5. Race Readiness not surfaced as a default metric — too abstract, unreliable early in training
  6. Plan target TSS exists per-week from plan_engine.ts
  7. No empty-state shaming — beginner weeks with 0–60 TSS get neutral, encouraging copy

  ---
  B) The ONE Sentence Narrative

  The Stats page communicates exactly one sentence. Everything else is evidence for that sentence.

  "Your load is [building / holding steady / easing off] — [you're building well / ease into next week / protect
  recovery before next week]."

  This is a 3 × 3 matrix (direction × ACWR status = 9 specific sentences). It is not a static tagline — it updates on
  tab focus. It sits in 16px medium weight, muted text, directly below the page heading. It IS the page. The chart is
  proof. The cards are the number.

