  ---
  D) Toggle vs Progressive Disclosure — Decision

  Option 1: Simple / Advanced Toggle

  Pros: Clean mental model, easy to A/B test, avoids scroll depth anxiety
  Cons: Requires toggle placement (awkward on mobile headers), two layout trees to maintain, beginners may never find
  it, users forget which mode they're in

  Option 2: One Page with Progressive Disclosure Sections

  Pros: Natural on mobile (scroll = explore), no mode state, users discover advanced content organically, single layout
   tree, pattern familiar from Apple Health and Strava
  Cons: Advanced users can't jump directly to PMC, no "I want everything" affordance

  Decision: Option 2 — Progressive Disclosure.

  Rationale: Mosaic's modal user is a beginner-intermediate runner who will never tap an "Advanced" toggle. A binary
  toggle creates a cognitive question ("which mode am I supposed to use?") that gets in the way of trust. Scroll is
  free. Power users find the accordion through curiosity; beginners never feel excluded from a "Simple" box. Persistent
   accordion state (localStorage) means power users don't re-expand every session.

