  G) Engineering Handoff

  Raw Fields Required

  // Per Week (last 8 weeks)
  week.tss            // number | null — actual TSS (null if week not started)
  week.plannedTSS     // number — plan target TSS
  week.actualKm       // number — running km logged
  week.plannedKm      // number — plan target km
  week.crossTSS       // number — cross-training TSS contribution
  week.crossKm        // number — cross-training km equivalent (volumeTransfer applied)
  week.zoneSplit      // { base: number, threshold: number, intensity: number } | null
  week.iTrimp         // number | null — for zone classification fallback
  week.startDate      // ISO string — for x-axis labels
  week.isComplete     // boolean

  // Global state
  s.biologicalSex     // for iTRIMP sex-correction factor
  s.athleteTier       // 'beginner' | 'intermediate' | 'advanced' | 'high_volume'
  injuryEngine.returnToRun  // boolean
  injuryEngine.currentRisk  // InjuryRisk — used for F6 banner trigger only

  Computed Fields

  // CTL at end of each week (already in fitness-model.ts)
  CTL_n = CTL_{n-1} × (1 − 1/42) + TSS_n × (1/42)
  // Seed: 0, or onboarding estimate if available

  // ATL per week
  ATL_n = ATL_{n-1} × (1 − 1/7) + TSS_n × (1/7)

  // Training Intensity (card value)
  trainingIntensity = currentWeek.tss / CTL_current
  displayValue = ${Math.round((trainingIntensity - 1) * 100)}% vs baseline
  // Special: if CTL < 20 → null → show "—", status "Building"

  // Narrative direction
  recent3Avg = avg(weeks[-3..-1].tss)
  historic5Avg = avg(weeks[-8..-4].tss)
  direction = recent3Avg > historic5Avg × 1.05 ? 'building'
            : recent3Avg < historic5Avg × 0.95 ? 'easing'
            : 'steady'

  // Narrative action — from ACWR status (already computed)
  // 3 × 3 matrix → 9 specific sentence endings

  // Consistency score
  consistency = (weeks where actualTSS >= plannedTSS × 0.70).length / totalWeeks × 100

  // Zone proportions (for Advanced bar)
  zonePct = {
    base: week.zoneSplit.base / week.tss,
    threshold: week.zoneSplit.threshold / week.tss,
    intensity: week.zoneSplit.intensity / week.tss
  }

  // Plan zone proportions
  // Stored per week from plan_engine — if not available, use sport × intensity defaults
  // from LOAD_PROFILES in workouts/load.ts

  Acceptance Criteria (PM/Designer sign-off)

  1. 5-second scan: Cover the bottom half of the screen with your thumb — the card labels and the top of the chart
  communicate a clear status without scrolling.
  2. No full-red screen: In no scenario does the entire chart, card background, or page header turn red. Red appears
  only as a bar cap segment.
  3. Narrative updates on tab focus: Not only on app open — the narrative sentence recomputes when the user navigates
  to Stats.
  4. Cross-training week not empty: A week with 0 running km but 60 cross-training TSS shows a full-height blue+purple
  bar.
  5. Beginner never sees "High load": An 8-week dataset with max 45 TSS/week, following plan, never produces an orange
  or red status pill.
  6. Tooltips in bounds: Tapping any bar on a 375px screen shows a tooltip that does not overflow either edge.
  7. Zone disabled state: When week.zoneSplit is null for all 8 weeks, the Zone Breakdown option in the switcher is
  visually disabled with explanatory copy — not a crash or empty bar.
  8. Return-to-run banner: When injuryEngine.returnToRun === true, the amber banner appears before the chart and the
  Training Intensity card shows "Return protocol" pill.

  ---
  H) Self-Critique + Revision

  5 Ways This Could Still Confuse Users or Look Busy

  1. "Training Intensity" sounds like effort-per-workout, not week-vs-baseline. A runner might read "+12% vs baseline"
  and think it means they ran harder than usual today, not that their weekly load is elevated.
  2. Two collapsed sections ("How it's calculated" and "⚙ Advanced stats") are visually similar on first scroll. A user
   who taps the first one and gets explainer bullets may think they've found everything and never discover the training
   bars.
  3. The CTL line disappears before week 4 (F1 edge state) but nothing explains this to users who open the Stats tab on
   day 1. They just see floating bars with no reference — which looks like a broken chart.
  4. The zone proportional bar (Advanced) with divergence text works only if users know what "plan zone targets" means.
   A user who doesn't know their plan specifies 75% base work will not understand why a ⚠ is appearing at 70% base.
  5. The narrative sentence matrix (3 × 3 = 9 variants) is invisible to engineers without a table. Without explicit
  copy for all 9 cells, this will be implemented as 2–3 generic strings, defeating the purpose.

